<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2005-05-26</DATELINE><TITLE>Biochip sensors for the rapid and sensitive detection of viral disease</TITLE><BODY>Recent advances in DNA and protein microarray methodology and the emerging technology of cell-based sensors have massively increased the speed and sensitivity with which we can detect viral infections. The advantages of the multi-parameter microarray technologies could be combined with the speed and sensitivity of cell-based systems to give 'cell-omic' sensors.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>